Explore the repo with your tools (Read, Grep, Bash). Read the files the ticket likely touches, related modules, their tests, and any CLAUDE.md. Then:

1. Write a high-level plan: what changes, in what order, and why. Prose only — NO file-level detail, NO code.
2. Break the work into an ordered list of changes. Each change is one bounded, independently reviewable unit of work. Prefer 1–6 changes; fewer is better.
3. Surface only BLOCKING questions, in these categories: ambiguity, missing context, scope/non-goals. Strong bias toward ZERO questions — resolve everything you can from the ticket, its goals, the repo, and CLAUDE.md. Never ask more than 6; if you would, the ticket is under-specified — say so in the highest-priority question instead.
